Infection with _Perkinsus olseni_, New Zealand
----------------------------------------------
Information received on 2 Sep 2014 from Dr Matthew Stone, director Animal and Animal Products, Standards Branch, Ministry for Primary Industries, Wellington, New Zealand

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 27 Aug 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 31 Aug 2014
Report date: 1 Sep 2014
Date event resolved: 1 Sep 2014
Reason for notification: change in epidemiology
New disease agent: no
New vector: no
New host species: [see epidemiological comment: "This is the 1st detection of _Perkinsus olseni_ in New Zealand green-lipped mussels." - Mod.CRD]
Increased pathogenicity: no
Zoonotic impact: no
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Perkinsus olseni_
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Nelson, Nelson, Nelson-Marlborough
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Aug 2014
Outbreak status: resolved (1 Sep 2014)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Water type: salt water
Population type: farmed
Production system: semi-closed
Affected animals:
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
New Zealand green-lipped mussel (_Perna canaliculus_) / 0 per cent / 0 per cent / - / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: _Perna canaliculus_ broodstock at aquaculture facility

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments
An aquaculture facility notified the Ministry for Primary Industries of a suspected detection of the protozoan parasite _Perkinsus olseni_ in a New Zealand green-lipped mussel (_Perna canaliculus_). The notification was based on histopathological findings during routine health monitoring by the aquaculture facility. No unusual mortality or signs of ill health have been observed in _Perna canaliculus_ at the facility. New Zealand's national animal health laboratory verified the presence of perkinsus by histopathology and confirmed _P. olseni_ via conventional PCR and sequencing. This is the 1st detection of _P. olseni_ in New Zealand green-lipped mussels. _P. olseni_ is known to occur in wild populations of the bivalves _Austrovenus stutchburyi_ (Veneridae), _Macomona liliana_ (Tellinidae), _Barbatia novaezelandiae_ (Arcidae), and _Paphies australis_ (Mesodesmatidae), as well as farmed and wild populations of _Haliotis iris_ (Haliotidae) in the North Island of New Zealand.

Control measures
Measures applied: no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Investigation and Diagnostic Centre (IDC), Wallaceville (national laboratory) / New Zealand green-lipped mussel (_Perna canaliculus_) / gene sequencing / 1 Sep 2014 / Positive
Investigation and Diagnostic Centre (IDC), Wallaceville (national laboratory) / New Zealand green-lipped mussel (_Perna canaliculus_) / histopathological examination / 31 Aug 2014 / Positive
Investigation and Diagnostic Centre (IDC), Wallaceville (national laboratory) / New Zealand green-lipped mussel (_Perna canaliculus_) / real-time PCR / 1 Sep 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

